,"type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Welsh   Vaughan  .","Chinese: variant of   Wong  .","Cambodian: written វ៉ុន, unexplained."],"variants":[{"name":"Vaughan","meanings":["Welsh: from <i>fychan</i>, a lenited form of <i>bychan</i>, a diminutive of <i>bach</i> ‘little’. This was often used to distinguish the younger of two bearers of the same personal name, typically the son of a father with the same name."]}]},{"name":"Eschenbach","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: habitational name from any of several places so named."],"variants":[{"name":"Eschenbacher","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt.","German: habitational name for someone from any of various places called   Eschenbach  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter I. von Eschenbach was born in 1125, in Hausen am Albis, Zürich, Switzerland as the son of Dietrich von Eschenbach. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Adelheid von Geroldseck. He died on 24 December 1180, in Hausen, Hausen am Albis, Zürich, Switzerland, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1125–24 December 1180":"1125–24. detsember 1180","1125–1180":"1125–1180","1115–1168":"1115–1168","1146–1249":"1146–1249","1150–1187":